1. Being totally dedicated to and fully aligned with the Phillips Corporation Vision, Mission, and Phillips Community Standard;
 2. Guaranteeing that Phillips has the best payroll process in the business by being aware of developments in payroll technologies and always being 100% compliant in all aspects of the ever changing regulations;
 3. Continuously evaluating our practices and policies as they relate to payroll and CE! Responsibilities ensuring that they are in line with Phillips culture and values, as well as the most efficient and cost-effective methods available to the industry;
 4. Ensuring full legal compliance to eliminate the potential for unnecessary obstacles to success;
 5. Being an expert on benefits and provide only the best benefit opportunities for our Partners and educating them on how to maximize their benefits potential; Creating and maintaining a great relationship with all benefit carriers;
 6. Continuously evaluating our practices, policies and culture to ensure our processes are in line with our values, as well as are the most efficient and cost-effective methods available;
 7. Establishing and maintaining the most effective up-to-date, partner friendly HRIS, allowing partners easy access to their information.
 8. Being irrevocably in the learning mode and having an insatiable curiosity about my role and mission, and expecting the same of anyone who comes in contact with me.
 9. Only hiring those whose purpose in life is aligned with our mission/vision/CPS and who are propelled by their purpose to be aggressively in the learning mode and irrevocably on the path to virtuosity;
 10. Ensuring we have a pipeline of great candidates to pull from at any time, so that hiring time is six weeks or less, thus increasing the productivity of our teams because they are never void of the talent they need to accomplish company goals.

